abilities.name: Conductivity
abilities.text: Whenever your opponent attaches an Energy card from his or her hand to a Pokemon, this power does 10 damage to that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.) This power stops working if you have more than 1 Dark Ampharos in play or while Dark Ampharos is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Shock Bolt
attacks.text: Discard all Lightning Energy cards attached to Dark Ampharos or this attack does nothing.

abilities.name: Surprise Bite
abilities.text: When you play Dark Crobat from your hand, you may choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This power does 20 damage to that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.)

attacks.name: Dark Drain
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each of your opponent's Pokemon. For each heads, this attack does 10 damage to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance. Remove a number of damage counters from Dark Crobat equal to the damage dealt. If Dark Crobat has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.

attacks.name: Tusk Toss
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, flip a coin. If heads, return the Defending Pokemon and all cards attached to it to your opponent's hand. If tails, your opponent chooses 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon and switches it with the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Gouge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.

attacks.name: Psysplash
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon for each Energy card attached to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

abilities.name: Scare
abilities.text: As long as Dark Feraligatr is your Active Pokemon, all of your opponent's Baby Pokemon Powers stop working and your opponent's Baby Pokemon can't attack. This power stops working while Dark Feraligatr is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Crushing Blow
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon has any Energy cards attached to it, flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of those cards and discard it.

abilities.name: Deep Sleep
abilities.text: As long as any Dark Gengar are in play, a player flips 2 coins for each of his or her Pokemon that is Asleep at the end of each turn. If either of them is tails, that Pokemon is still Asleep. This power stops working if Dark Gengar is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Pull In
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, you may choose 1 of them and switch it with the Defending Pokemon (before doing damage or other effects of this attack). Either way, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Eerie Howl
attacks.text: If your opponent's Bench isn't full, look at his or her hand. If your opponent has any Baby Pokemon or Basic Pokemon there, choose 1 of them and put it on his or her Bench. Then, switch it with the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Dark Fire
attacks.text: If there are any Darkness Energy cards attached to Dark Houndoom, discard 1 of them and this attack does 30 damage plus 20 more damage (plus 10 more damage for the Darkness Energy you discarded). If there aren't any, this attack does 30 damage.

abilities.name: Spatial Distortion
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, choose a Stadium card from your discard pile and put it into play. (If there's already a Stadium card in play, discard it.) This power can't be used if Dark Porygon2 is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Curve Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done by attacks to Dark Porygon2 during your opponent's next turn. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)

attacks.name: Threaten
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, look at your opponent's hand. If he or she has any Trainer cards there, choose 1 of them. Your opponent shuffles that card into his or her deck.

attacks.name: Rushing Flames
attacks.text: You may discard any number of Fire Energy cards attached to your Pokemon. Flip a coin for each Fire Energy card discarded in this way. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Mountain Smasher
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Fighting Energy cards attached to Dark Tyranitar. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads. Then, for each heads, discard the top card from your opponent's deck.

attacks.name: Fling Away
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, this attack does 30 damage instead of 50 and choose 1 of those Benched Pokemon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

abilities.name: Drive Off
abilities.text: As long as Light Arcanine is your Active Pokemon, once during your turn (before your attack), if your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, he or she chooses 1 of them and switches it with the Defending Pokemon. This power can't be used while Light Arcanine is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Gentle Flames
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon is a Baby Pokemon, this attack does 10 damage instead of 50. If the Defending Pokemon is a Basic Pokemon, this attack does 30 damage instead of 50.

attacks.name: Bubble
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Bubble Jump
attacks.text: If you have any Benched Pokemon, flip a coin. If heads, take 2 Energy cards attached to Light Azumarill and attach them to 1 of your Benched Pokemon. Then return Light Azumarill and all cards attached to it to your hand.

abilities.name: Miraculous Wind
abilities.text: As long as Light Dragonite is your Active Pokemon, each Special Energy card provides Colorless Energy instead of its usual type and its other effects stop working. This power stops working while Light Dragonite is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Light Wave
attacks.text: Prevent all effects of attacks, other than damage, done to Light Dragonite during your opponent's next turn.

abilities.name: Gift
abilities.text: When you play Light Togetic from your hand, your opponent may search his or her deck for a Pokemon Tool card, show that card to you, and put it into his or her hand. Either way, you may do the same, and then each player who searched shuffles his or her deck.

attacks.name: Sweet Kiss
attacks.text: Your opponent may draw a card.

name: Miracle Energy
rules: You can't have more than 1 Miracle Energy in your deck. Attach Miracle Energy to 1 of your Shining or Light Pokemon. At the end of your turn, discard Miracle Energy. While in play, Miracle Energy counts as every type of Energy but provides only 2 Energy at a time.

attacks.name: Entangle
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, choose 1 of them and switch it with the Defending Pokemon, then flip a coin. If heads, the new Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Poison Bind
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned. Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat until the end of your opponent's next turn and if the effect of an attack, Pokemon Power, or Trainer card would change that player's Active Pokemon, that part of the effect does nothing.

abilities.name: Hot Plate
abilities.text: As long as Dark Magcargo is your Active Pokemon, whenever a player puts a Baby Pokemon or Basic Pokemon onto his or her Bench from his or her hand, this power does 10 damage to that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.) This power stops working if Dark Magcargo is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Ball of Flame
attacks.text: You may discard a Fire Energy card attached to Dark Magcargo when you use this attack. If you do and if your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, choose 1 of them and this attack does 20 damage to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

attacks.name: Prehistoric Water
attacks.text: If your opponent has any evolved Pokemon in play, choose 1 of them and flip a coin. If heads, your opponent takes the highest Stage Evolution card on that Pokemon and shuffles it into his or her deck.

attacks.name: Dark Tentacle
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't evolve except from effects of attacks or Pokemon Powers. (Benching that Pokemon ends this effect.)

abilities.name: Cunning
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, look at the top card of your opponent's deck. Then, you may have your opponent shuffle his or her deck. This power can't be used if Dark Slowking is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Mind Shock
attacks.text: Don't apply Weakness or Resistance for this attack.

attacks.name: Provoke
attacks.text: Look at your opponent's hand. If he or she has any Baby Pokemon and/or Basic Pokemon there, you may put any number of them onto your opponent's Bench (as long as there's room). Then, your opponent looks at your hand. If you have any Baby Pokemon and/or Basic Pokemon there, your opponent may put any number of them onto your Bench (as long as there's room).

attacks.name: Battle Frenzy
attacks.text: For each Pokemon in play (yours and your opponent's), flip a coin. For each heads, this attack does 20 damage to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack.

attacks.name: Healing Light
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from each of your Pokemon that has any damage counters on it.

attacks.name: Protective Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Light Dragonair.

attacks.name: Searchlight
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, each player may choose a card from his or her discard pile and put it into his or her hand.

attacks.name: Spark
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, choose 1 of them and this attack does 10 damage to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

attacks.name: Flash Touch
attacks.text: If you have any Benched Pokemon, switch 1 of them with Light Ledian. As long as that Pokemon is your Active Pokemon, it can't become Asleep, Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned. (All other effects of attacks, Pokemon Powers, and Trainer cards still happen.)

attacks.name: Comet Punch
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

abilities.name: Tag Team
abilities.text: When you play Light Machamp from your hand, if it is on your Bench, remove 3 damage counters from your Active Pokemon. If it has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them. Then, switch Light Machamp with your Active Pokemon.

attacks.name: Beatdown
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon has Dark in its name or is a Darkness Pokemon, flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 100 damage instead of 50.

abilities.name: Fluffy Wool
abilities.text: During your opponent's turn, if Light Piloswine is your Active Pokemon and is damaged by your opponent's attack (even if it's Knocked Out), flip a coin. If heads, the attacking Pokemon is now Asleep. This power stops working if Light Piloswine is already Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed when your opponent attacks.

attacks.name: Knock Over
attacks.text: If there is a Stadium card in play, you may discard it.

name: Unown [G]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Give]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown [G], Unown [I], Unown [V], and Unown [E] on your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokemon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Unown [H]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Help]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown [H], Unown [E], Unown [L], and Unown [P] on your Bench, you may shuffle your hand into your deck, then draw a new hand of the same number of cards.

name: Unown [W]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Want]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown [W], Unown [A], Unown [N], and Unown [T] on your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, put a Trainer card from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Unown [X]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [XXXXX]
abilities.text: Whenever 1 of your Pokemon with Unown in its name uses its Hidden Power attack, flip a coin until you get tails. That attack does 10 more damage for each heads. If you have more than 1 Unown [X] in play, use only 1 [XXXXX] each turn.

attacks.name: Doubleslap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Egg Toss
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Clamping Jaw
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn. If the Defending Pokemon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing. (Benching either Pokemon ends this effect.)

attacks.name: Triple Headbutt
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: MAX Burst
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Energy cards attached to your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: High Voltage
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent can't play Trainer cards during his or her next turn.

attacks.name: Stun Wave
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon has a Pokemon Power, that power stops working until the end of your next turn.

attacks.name: Armor Up
attacks.text: Until the end of your next turn, if Dark Forretress would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, flip a coin. If heads, Dark Forretress is not Knocked Out and its remaining HP become 10 instead.

attacks.name: Explosion
attacks.text: Dark Forretress does 60 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Call Back
attacks.text: Put a Baby Pokemon or Basic Pokemon card from your opponent's discard pile onto his or her Bench. Put 1 damage counter on that Pokemon. (You can't use this attack if your Bench is full.)

attacks.name: Surround
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep. If tails, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Water Cannon
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 10 damage for each Water Energy card attached to Dark Omanyte. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance. You can't do more than 30 damage in this way.

attacks.name: Rock Tackle
attacks.text: Dark Pupitar does 10 damage to itself. Dark Pupitar can't use this attack during your next turn.

attacks.name: Explosive Evolution
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance. Then, search your deck for an Evolution card named Dark Tyranitar and put it on Dark Pupitar. (This counts as evolving Dark Pupitar.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Incinerate
attacks.text: Show the top card of your opponent's deck to all players. If it's a Trainer card, discard it.

attacks.name: Rushing Magma
attacks.text: Discard the top 5 cards of your deck. (If there are fewer than 5 cards in your deck, discard all of them.) This attack does 20 damage for each Fire Energy card you discarded in this way.

attacks.name: Dark Song
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep. If tails, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Slap Awake
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon is Asleep or Confused, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage. Then, the Defending Pokemon is no longer Asleep or Confused.

attacks.name: Charging Horn
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage. If tails, this attack does 30 damage.

attacks.name: One-Two Kick
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Heel Drop
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Corner
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Lunge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Expand
attacks.text: All damage done to Jigglypuff during your opponent's next turn is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Freezing Breath
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed. If tails, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Ice Pillar
attacks.text: Until the end of your opponent's next turn, as long as Light Dewgong is your Active Pokemon, prevent all damage done by attacks to your Benched Pokemon. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)

attacks.name: Warm Up
attacks.text: If you have any benched Pokemon, search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to 1 of them. Then shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Burning Flame
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, discard a Fire Energy card attached to Light Flareon or this attack does nothing. This attack does 30 damage plus 20 damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Flipper Stroke
attacks.text: Your opponent looks at the top 3 cards of his or her deck. If any of them are basic Energy cards, he or she may show any number of them to you and put them into his or her hand. You do the same. Either way, each player shuffles his or her deck.

attacks.name: Core Blast
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage plus 20 more damage for each Special Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Pulse Guard
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, whenever 30 or more damage is done to Light Jolteon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), prevent that damage. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)

attacks.name: Thunder Needle
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads. If you get 2 or more heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Return Home
attacks.text: If you have any Benched Pokemon, shuffle 1 of them and all cards attached to it into your deck.

attacks.name: Gentle Kick
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon has no damage counters on it, this attack does 40 damage. If it has any, this attack does 20 damage.

attacks.name: Guiding Flame
attacks.text: Put a Baby Pokemon or a Basic Pokemon card from your discard pile onto your Bench. (You can't use this attack if your Bench is full.)

attacks.name: Fire Blast
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy card attached to Light Ninetales in order to use this attack.

attacks.name: Fish Out
attacks.text: Your opponent may choose up to 3 Baby Pokemon, Basic Pokemon, and/or Evolution cards from his or her discard pile and shuffle them into his or her deck. Either way, you may do the same.

attacks.name: Splash About
attacks.text: If there are more Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon than to Light Slowbro, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage. If not, this attack does 20 damage.

attacks.name: Wash Away
attacks.text: If you have any Benched Pokemon, flip a coin. If heads, remove all damage counters from 1 of your Benched Pokemon and discard all Energy cards attached to it.

attacks.name: Hypnoshower
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep. Remove 1 damage counter from each Benched Pokemon (yours and your opponent's) with any damage counters on it.

attacks.name: Mysterious Wing
attacks.text: Your opponent may choose a Baby Pokemon, Basic Pokemon, or Evolution card from his or her discard pile and put it into his or her hand. Either way, you may do the same.

attacks.name: Synchronize
attacks.text: If Light Venomoth and the Defending Pokemon have a different number of Energy cards attached to them, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Evolution Song
attacks.text: Your opponent may choose 1 of his or her Pokemon and search his or her deck for a card that evolves from that Pokemon. Your opponent attaches that card to that Pokemon. This counts as evolving that Pokemon. Either way, you may do the same, and then each player who searched shuffles his or her deck.

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Scyther.

attacks.name: Charm
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon attacks during your opponent's next turn, any damage it does is reduced by 10 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Spike Ball Tackle
attacks.text: Togepi does 10 damage to itself.

name: Unown [C]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Chase]
abilities.text: As long as Unown [C] is your Active Pokemon, whenever your opponent's Active Pokemon tries to retreat, flip a coin. If heads, put 1 damage counter on that Pokemon. Apply Weakness and Resistance.

name: Unown [P]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Perform]
abilities.text: If an attack damaged Unown [P] during your opponent's last turn and Unown [P] was your Active Pokemon, Unown [P]'s Hidden Power attack does that much more damage to the Defending Pokemon. This power can be used even if Unown [P] is Confused.

name: Unown [Q]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Quicken]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to any of your Pokemon with Unown in its name during your opponent's next turn. If you have more than 1 Unown [Q] in play, use only 1 [Quicken] each turn. This power can be used even if Unown [Q] is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

name: Unown [Z]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Zoom]
abilities.text: As long as Unown [Z] is Benched, you pay no Energy cost to retreat a Pokemon with Unown in its name.

attacks.name: Smokescreen
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Ink Blast
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to Dark Octillery but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

attacks.name: Tentacle Wrap
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed. If tails, during your opponent's next turn, your opponent pays Colorless more to retreat the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Shed
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from Dratini.

attacks.name: Fury Attack
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Sleep Powder
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Psyshock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Nightmare
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Tail Bite
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Stun Poison
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Dodge
attacks.text: If Hitmonchan would be damaged by an attack during your opponent's next turn, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that attack's damage done to Hitmonchan. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)

attacks.name: Leer
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon can't attack during your opponent's next turn. (Benching or evolving either Pokemon ends this effect.)

attacks.name: Swift
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Pokemon Powers, or any other effects on the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Reflected Sunlight
attacks.text: Attach up to 2 Grass Energy cards from your hand to 1 of your Grass Pokemon.

attacks.name: Giant Wave
attacks.text: Mantine can't attack during your next turn.

attacks.name: Crushing Step
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.

attacks.name: Migraine
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused. If tails, Psyduck is now Confused.

attacks.name: Fury Strikes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: Seel does 10 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Sunbathe
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, remove all damage counters from Sunkern. Search your deck for a card that evolves from Sunkern and attach that card to Sunkern. This counts as evolving Sunkern. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Generate Cold
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Water Gun
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Totodile but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

name: Unown [L]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Laugh]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, each player shuffles his or her deck. This power can be used even if Unown [L] is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

name: Unown [S]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Search]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may look at 1 of your Prize cards. Return that Prize card face down. This power can be used even if Unown [S] is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

name: Unown [T]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Tell]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, look at your opponent's hand and show your hand to your opponent. This power can be used even if Unown [T] is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

name: Unown [V]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Vanish]
abilities.text: When you play Unown [V] from your hand, you may flip a coin. If heads, return 1 of your Pokemon with Unown in its name (other than Unown [V]) to your hand. (Discard all cards attached to that card.)

attacks.name: Poisonpowder
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.text: Discard 1 Fire Energy card attached to Vulpix in order to use this attack.

name: Broken Ground Gym
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.
Each player pays Colorless more to retreat a Baby Pokemon or Basic Pokemon.

name: EXP.ALL
rules: Attach EXP.ALL to 1 of your Pokemon that doesn't have a Pokemon Tool attached to it.

During your opponent's turn, if your Active Pokemon would be Knocked Out by your opponent's attack, you may take 1 of the basic Energy cards attached to your Active Pokemon and attach it to the Pokemon with EXP.ALL attached to it. If you do, discard EXP.ALL.

name: Impostor Professor Oak's Invention
rules: Look at your opponent's Prize cards. You may have your opponent shuffle them into his or her deck. If you do, your opponent takes that many cards from the top of his or her deck and sets them aside as his or her new Prize cards (without looking at them).

name: Radio Tower
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.
Once during each player's turn (before attacking), that player may look at the top 2 cards of his or her deck and put them back in the same order.

name: Thought Wave Machine
rules: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, return an Energy card attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon to your opponent's hand. If the Pokemon has fewer attached Energy cards than that, return all of them to your opponent's hand. Your turn is over now (you don't get to attack).

name: Counterattack Claws
rules: Attach Counterattack Claws to 1 of your Pokemon that doesn't have a Pokemon Tool attached to it.

During your opponent's turn, if the Pokemon Counterattack Claws is attached to is your Active Pokemon and an opponent's attack damages it (even if it is Knocked Out), flip a coin. If heads, put 2 damage counters on the Defending Pokemon. Then, discard Counterattack Claws.

name: Energy Amplifier
rules: Choose an Energy card in your hand, show it to your opponent, and shuffle it into your deck. Then flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards. Show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Energy Stadium
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.
Once during each player's turn (before attacking), that player may flip a coin. If heads, that player puts a basic Energy card from his or her discard pile into his or her hand.

name: Lucky Stadium
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.
Once during each player's turn (before attacking), that player may flip a coin. If heads, that player draws a card.

name: Magnifier
rules: Attach Magnifier to 1 of your Pokemon. At the end of your turn, discard Magnifier. If the Pokemon Magnifier is attached to attacks, don't apply Resistance for that attack.

name: Pokemon Personality Test
rules: Put an Evolution card from your hand face down in front of you. Your opponent guesses whether it is a Pokemon card with Light in its name, a Pokemon card with Dark in its name, or neither one. Flip the card over. If your opponent guessed right, he or she draws 3 cards. If your opponent guessed wrong, you draw 3 cards. Either way, return the card to your hand.

name: Team Rocket's Evil Deeds
rules: Look at your opponent's hand and choose a card there. Your opponent shuffles that card into his or her deck. Then, your opponent may draw up to 2 cards.

name: Heal Powder
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, your Active Pokemon is no longer Asleep, Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned and remove 2 damage counters from it. If your Active Pokemon has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.

name: Mail from Bill
rules: You can't play this card if you have 5 or more cards in your hand (including this one). Draw cards until you have exactly 4 cards in your hand.

name: Shining Celebi
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Celebi in your deck.

attacks.name: Healing Water
attacks.text: Remove a number of damage counters from 1 of your Benched Pokemon equal to the number of Water Energy cards attached to Shining Celebi. If the Pokemon has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.

attacks.name: Miracle Leaf
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon. If you get 1 or more heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep, Confused, or Poisoned (your choice).

name: Shining Charizard
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Charizard in your deck.

attacks.name: White-hot Flame
attacks.text: Discard 1 Fire Energy card and 1 Lightning Energy card attached to Shining Charizard or this attack does nothing. Flip a coin. If tails, Shining Charizard does 30 damage to itself.

name: Shining Kabutops
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Kabutops in your deck.

attacks.name: Lightning Cut
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage and does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) If tails, this attack does 30 damage and Shining Kabutops does 10 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Water Slash
attacks.text: Does 50 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Shining Kabutops but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. Don't apply Resistance.

name: Shining Mewtwo
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Mewtwo in your deck.

attacks.name: Reflect Shield
attacks.text: If an attack does damage to Shining Mewtwo during your opponent's next turn (even if Shining Mewtwo is Knocked Out), flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Shining Mewtwo from that attack (any other effects of attacks still happen) and do 20 damage to the attacking Pokemon.

attacks.name: Psyburst
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy card attached to Shining Mewtwo or this attack does nothing. This attack does 40 damage plus 10 damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon.

name: Shining Noctowl
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Noctowl in your deck.

attacks.name: Flashing Eyes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. If exactly 1 is heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep. If exactly 2 are heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused. If all 3 are heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Shining Raichu
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Raichu in your deck.

attacks.name: Thundersquall
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, choose 1 of them and this attack does 10 damage to that Pokemon for each Water Energy attached to Shining Raichu. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Shining Steelix
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Steelix in your deck.

attacks.name: Crushing Earth
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each Benched Pokemon (yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) If tails, this attack does nothing. Either way, Shining Steelix can't attack during your next turn.

name: Shining Tyranitar
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Tyranitar in your deck.

attacks.name: Mountain Crush
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, your opponent discards the top card from his or her deck.

attacks.name: Destructive Fire
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each Fire Energy card attached to Shining Tyranitar. For each heads, discard a Fire Energy card attached to Shining Tyranitar or this attack does nothing. Then, for each heads, choose an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon and discard it. If it has fewer Energy cards than that, remove all of them.
